---
import ToolPage from '../layouts/ToolPage.astro';
---
<ToolPage
  title="Case Converter, camelCase, snake_case, kebab-case &amp; more | KB Cafe"
  description="Convert text between camelCase, PascalCase, snake_case, CONSTANT_CASE, kebab-case, Title Case and more, all at once, copy any. Free, fast, client-side."
  path="/case-converter"
  eyebrow="Text"
  h1="Case Converter"
  tagline="Type anything and get it in every case at once, camelCase, snake_case, kebab-case, CONSTANT_CASE and more. Copy any line. Runs entirely in your browser."
>
  <div class="pane" style="margin-bottom:18px">
    <div class="pane-label"><span>Your text</span><button class="link-btn" id="sample">load sample</button></div>
    <textarea id="in" class="ta" style="min-height:96px" spellcheck="false" placeholder="Type a phrase, variable name, or heading…"></textarea>
  </div>
  <div class="cases" id="out"></div>
  <p class="status" id="status"></p>

  <Fragment slot="explainer">
    <h2>Every naming convention, one paste</h2>
    <p>
      Paste a phrase or an identifier and this tool re-tokenizes it, splitting on spaces, hyphens, underscores,
      and the boundaries inside <code>camelCase</code> and <code>PascalCase</code>: then re-joins it in each common
      convention. It detects word boundaries intelligently, so <code>getUserID</code>, <code>get_user_id</code>, and
      <code>get user id</code> all produce the same set of outputs.
    </p>

    <h3>The conventions</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>camelCase</code>: first word lower, the rest capitalized. Common for JS/Java variables.</li>
      <li><code>PascalCase</code>: every word capitalized. Types, classes, React components.</li>
      <li><code>snake_case</code>: lowercase, underscores. Python, Ruby, SQL columns.</li>
      <li><code>CONSTANT_CASE</code>: uppercase snake. Constants and env vars.</li>
      <li><code>kebab-case</code>: lowercase, hyphens. URLs, CSS classes, file names.</li>
      <li><code>Title Case</code> / <code>Sentence case</code>: for headings and prose.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <details class="faq"><summary>How are word boundaries detected?</summary>
      <p>It splits on spaces, <code>-</code>, <code>_</code>, <code>.</code>, and <code>/</code>, and also on lower-to-upper transitions (<code>userName</code> → <code>user</code> + <code>name</code>) and acronym edges (<code>parseJSONData</code> → <code>parse</code> + <code>JSON</code> + <code>data</code>).</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Is my text uploaded?</summary>
      <p>No, conversion runs in your browser, so it works offline and nothing is sent anywhere.</p>
    </details>

    <h3>Related</h3>
    <p>Generating types? Try <a href="/json-to-typescript">JSON → TypeScript</a>. Slugging URLs for redirects? See the <a href="/htaccess-generator">.htaccess generator</a>.</p>
  </Fragment>
</ToolPage>

<style is:global> /* JS-created elements need unscoped CSS, see context-budget-analyzer */
  .link-btn{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--coral);background:none;border:0;cursor:pointer}
  .link-btn:hover{color:var(--coral-deep);text-decoration:underline}
  .cases{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px}
  .case-row{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;background:var(--cream);border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:10px 12px 10px 15px}
  .case-row .lbl{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-soft);width:140px;flex-shrink:0}
  .case-row .val{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink);flex:1;overflow:auto;white-space:nowrap}
  .case-row .cp{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--coral);background:none;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:8px;padding:6px 11px;cursor:pointer;flex-shrink:0}
  .case-row .cp:hover{border-color:var(--ink);color:var(--ink)}
  .case-row .cp.done{color:#2f7d32;border-color:#2f7d32}
  @media(max-width:560px){.case-row{flex-wrap:wrap}.case-row .lbl{width:auto}.case-row .val{width:100%;order:3}}
</style>

<script is:inline>
  const $ = id => document.getElementById(id);
  const inEl = $('in'), out = $('out'), statusEl = $('status');
  const SAMPLE = 'KB Cafe, freshly brewed dev tools';

  function words(s){
    return String(s)
      .replace(/([a-z0-9])([A-Z])/g, '$1 $2')        // camel boundary
      .replace(/([A-Z]+)([A-Z][a-z])/g, '$1 $2')      // acronym boundary
      .replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]+/g, ' ')
      .trim().split(/\s+/).filter(Boolean).map(w => w.toLowerCase());
  }
  const cap = w => w.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + w.slice(1);
  const FORMATS = [
    ['camelCase',     w => w.map((x,i)=>i?cap(x):x).join('')],
    ['PascalCase',    w => w.map(cap).join('')],
    ['snake_case',    w => w.join('_')],
    ['CONSTANT_CASE', w => w.map(x=>x.toUpperCase()).join('_')],
    ['kebab-case',    w => w.join('-')],
    ['Train-Case',    w => w.map(cap).join('-')],
    ['dot.case',      w => w.join('.')],
    ['path/case',     w => w.join('/')],
    ['Title Case',    w => w.map(cap).join(' ')],
    ['Sentence case', w => w.length ? cap(w.join(' ')) : ''],
    ['lower case',    w => w.join(' ')],
    ['UPPER CASE',    w => w.map(x=>x.toUpperCase()).join(' ')],
  ];

  function render(){
    const w = words(inEl.value);
    out.innerHTML = '';
    if(!w.length){ statusEl.textContent=''; return; }
    FORMATS.forEach(([label, fn]) => {
      const val = fn(w);
      const row = document.createElement('div'); row.className = 'case-row';
      row.innerHTML = `<span class="lbl">${label}</span><span class="val"></span><button class="cp">copy</button>`;
      row.querySelector('.val').textContent = val;
      const btn = row.querySelector('.cp');
      btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
        try { await navigator.clipboard.writeText(val); } catch {}
        btn.textContent = 'copied'; btn.classList.add('done');
        setTimeout(() => { btn.textContent = 'copy'; btn.classList.remove('done'); }, 1100);
      });
      out.appendChild(row);
    });
    statusEl.className = 'status ok'; statusEl.textContent = `${w.length} word${w.length>1?'s':''} · ${FORMATS.length} formats`;
  }
  inEl.addEventListener('input', render);
  $('sample').addEventListener('click', () => { inEl.value = SAMPLE; render(); });
  inEl.value = SAMPLE; render();
</script>
